Building Training Content
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure OBS Studio for recording security awareness videos
Create professional training content using screen recording techniques
Design graphics and visual elements for training materials
Develop Python scripts to automate video processing workflows
Implement a complete content creation and distribution pipeline
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Fundamental Python programming knowledge
Understanding of file system operations
Familiarity with video file formats (MP4, AVI)
Basic security awareness concepts
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides pre-configured Ubuntu cloud machines with all necessary dependencies. Click Start Lab to access your environment.

Task 1: Installing and Configuring OBS Studio
Step 1: Install Required Software
# Update system and install OBS Studio
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y obs-studio ffmpeg v4l2loopback-dkms

# Install multimedia codecs and tools
sudo apt install -y ubuntu-restricted-extras imagemagick

# Create project directory structure
mkdir -p ~/security-training/{videos,graphics,scripts,processed}
cd ~/security-training
Step 2: Configure OBS Studio
# Launch OBS Studio
obs &
Manual Configuration in OBS:

Click Cancel on Auto-Configuration Wizard
Navigate to Settings > Output
Configure Recording settings:
Output Mode: Advanced
Recording Path: /home/student/security-training/videos
Recording Format: MP4
Encoder: x264
Bitrate: 5000 Kbps
Click Apply and OK
Step 3: Create Recording Scenes
Desktop Capture Scene:

In Scenes panel, click + button
Name: Desktop Demo
In Sources, click + > Screen Capture (XSHM)
Name: Full Desktop, select entire screen
Presenter Mode Scene:

Create new scene: Presenter Mode
Add Screen Capture (XSHM) source
Add Video Capture Device (V4L2) for webcam
Resize webcam to bottom-right corner (300x200 pixels)
